Please read this entirely before continuing so you fully understand that ATAK makes use of several Android permissions during the course of commonly used workflows.
None of this information from access provided by these permissions is collected by the TAK program office. No capability provided by these permissions are used while ATAK is not running.

The decision early on in the development of ATAK was to ask for these permissions up front instead of when the workflow was needed in order to provide for a consistent experience for the end users. Since it is not obvious why we request these permissions here is the list and rational for each. Some versions of Android may not prompt for all of these permissions. In addition the request for these permissions may be out of order.
Allow ATAK to take pictures and record video
Allow ATAK to access this devices location (Precise)

This application is a moving map capability that provides situational awareness based on your location provided by the devices GPS. For first responders and other users in the user experience workflows, precise positioning is used.
Plugins make use of either recording audio, provide for push to talk capability, and audio processing such as speech to text.
Allow ATAK to find, connect to, and determine the relative position of nearby devices
This is used for Bluetooth functionality within ATAK.
Allow ATAK to send you notifications
Used to provide Android notifications at the top left of the screen while the application is running.
Allow ATAK to make and manage phone calls

Within your network or enclave of TAK users, the phone number is attached to the point position location advertised by other users. This allows you to call that person without leaving the application.
Allow ATAK to access music and audio on this device
Allows for users to attach audio to markers in specific workflows that can be played back at a later time or shared with other TAK users on your network or enclave.
Allow ATAK to access photos and videos on this device
Allows for users to attach photos and videos to markers in specific workflows that can be played back at a later time or shared with other TAK users on your network or enclave.
Allow ATAK to send and view SMS messages
Allows for a text message to be sent when activating an Emergency Alert for cases if desired. Note that this functionality is only engaged if configured.

Enabling this feature will allow for the required permissions to be bypassed and still allow for ATAK to be run. The capabilities will be limited and this will not provide for an optimal user experience and is not recommended. Plugins may crash as they expect access to the permissions. Additionally, Android may remove previously approved permissions at any time degrading the user experience even further.
